
README:
-------

This directory is the place from which the Decay0 source code is extracted
from the original version and integrated in the 'genbb_help' source tree.

Cd in the 'decay0' directory:

   bash$ cd decay0 

Test the decay0 program with CERNLIB:

   Use the 'decay0_fixed.for' file because the original 'decay0.for' 
   does not support gfortran.

      bash$ gfortran decay0_fixed.for $(cernlib packlib mathlib) -o decay0_fixed

   Run the executable to check if it runs:

      bash$ ./decay0_fixed

Generate some sample plots:

      bash$ ./make_reference_samples

Generate some plots using the genbb_help tools and compare with the reference plots:

      bash$ ./make_validation_samples

  Display the plots (PS files) to be compared:
 
      bash$ $ ls -1 *.ps
      decay0_reference_plot.ps
      genbb_help_validation_plot.ps


===========================================================================

Package's maintener only:

  Generate genbb source files from the original 'decay0.for' program
  and add check stuff in 'decay0/src/' :

    bash$ ./prepare_decay0.sh -c ./decay0.for

  Check that it builds:

    bash$ cd src
    bash$ make 	      

Generate genbb source files from the original 'decay0.for' program
and install it in the official 'genbb_help' source tree:

    bash$ ./prepare_decay0.sh ./decay0.for

